          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657117504718-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657117504718-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 22-25 min or until the tomatoes are soft and slightly charred – these are your <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679671055073-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679671055073-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679671055073-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679671055073-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679671055073-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and add to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657117512048-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657117512048-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657117512048-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657117512048-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657117512048-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, give the <strong>one-pot spicy ‘Nduja & pepper orzo</strong> a good mix up, top with the <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong> and serve the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the orzo is looking a little dry</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped basil leaves</strong> and a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
